original_title: The Language of Dreams: Vol. 9: Snakes in Dreams
overview: Snakes have always played a large role in dream imagery; this compelling program explores the archetypal meanings of these creatures and the loaded associations they bring to nighttime experiences. Using vivid visual depictions, Jungian analyst Elizabeth Strahan takes viewers through intriguing interpretations, explaining how these dreams may lead dreamers on a personal voyage of new awareness.
title: The Language of Dreams: Vol. 9: Snakes in Dreams
